H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
AMENDING THE RULES OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES FOR THE YEARS
2023 AND 2024
Introduced By: Representatives Boylan, Cortvriend, Fogarty, Spears, Carson, Corvese,
Ackerman, Dawson, Knight, and Craven
Date Introduced: January 10, 2025
Referred To: House Rules
1 RESOLVED, that section 7(d) of the rules of the House of Representatives adopted by
2 the House of Representatives at its January session, A.D. 2023, entitled “House Resolution
3 Adopting the Rules of the House of Representatives for the years 2023 and 2024”, be and the
4 same is hereby amended to read as follows:
5 (d)(i) Unless the matter is submitted with the approval of the Speaker, a member may not
6 introduce more than eighteen (18) bills or resolutions during the course of a legislative session,
7 inclusive of bills introduced pursuant to subsection (iii) of this rule. This limitation shall not apply
8 to city or town bills, to bills for the reinstatement of corporate charters, to bills relating to the
9 solemnization of marriages, to ceremonial resolutions of congratulations or condolence, to
10 appropriations and budget bills, to bills creating or extending the reporting dates of study
11 commissions or to bills introduced on behalf of a study commission by the commission's
12 chairperson or other member with the approval of the Speaker.
13 (ii) All bills and resolutions shall be filed no later than February 16, 2023 27, 2025 (for
14 the 2023 2025 session) and February 15, 2024 12, 2026 (for the 2024 2026 session). The
15 provisions of this section shall not apply to city or town bills, to bills for the reinstatement of
16 corporate charters, to bills relating to the solemnization of marriages, to ceremonial resolutions of
17 congratulations or condolences, to appropriations and budget bills, or to bills to create or extend
