1 Speaker.
2 Further, a (iii) A member may introduce a public bill or resolution after this date in
3 February if one day previous to such introduction, the member shall have notified the House of
4 his or her intention to introduce such bill or resolution by reading the title and giving a brief
5 explanation of its purpose. A Subject to introduction limits imposed by this rule, a member may
6 avail himself or herself of the opportunity afforded by this rule three (3) times only in each
7 calendar year, but in no event after the fortieth (40th) legislative day unless the matter is submitted
8 with the approval of the Speaker. House Committees may, but shall not be obligated to, hear and
9 consider public bills or resolutions approved for introduction pursuant to this rule.
